    <body>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../Objects/SelectEndActionSummary.flsnp" />
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>how to select an end action for a cursor</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the frame.</li>
                    <li>Right-click the cursor. From the context menu, select <span class="Emphasis">Advanced &gt; Convert to Action Object</span>. This allows you to add End actions to the cursor.</li>
                    <li>Double-click the cursor shape. <MadCap:snippetText src="../Objects/ObjectPropertiesWindowPaneOpensMimic.flsnp" /></li>
                    <li>Expand the <span class="Emphasis">Action</span> section.</li>
                    <li>
                        <p>In the <span class="Emphasis">Event</span> field, select <span class="Emphasis">End</span>.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>In the <span class="Emphasis">Action</span> field, select the action that will take place when the event is performed: </p>
                        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="ActionDefinitionsObjectsOnly.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/StepsGeneral/ClickOK.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/StepsGeneral/SaveYourWork.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Shared/WhatsNext/WhatsNextAfterEdit.flsnp" />
        <p MadCap:conditions="General.RemoveFromTopicsThenDeleteThis">
            <MadCap:conceptLink term="Cursors;Actions" />
        </p>
    </body>
